com.intel.jndn.utils

Interface NameTree<T>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultNameTree

    public interface NameTree<T>
    Represent a tree of nodes, branching based on their component values
    Author:
    Andrew Brown, andrew.brown@intel.com

    • Method Summary

    • Method Detail

      • fullName

        net.named_data.jndn.Name fullName()
        Returns:
        the full name leading from the root of the tree to this node

      • lastComponent

        net.named_data.jndn.Name.Component lastComponent()
        Returns:
        the last component identifying this node; e.g. if the fullName() is /a/b/c for this node, this method must return c

      • content

        Optional<T> content()
        Returns:
        the optional content stored at this location in the tree

      • children

        Collection<NameTree<T>> children()
        Returns:
        the children of this node or an empty collection

      • parent

        NameTree<T> parent()
        Returns:
        the parent of this node; note that calling this on the root node will return null

      • insert

        NameTree<T> insert(net.named_data.jndn.Name name,
                   T content)
        Parameters:
        name - the full name leading to the location in the tree; if intervening nodes do not yet exist, they will be created
        content - the content to store at this location; this may overwrite previously existing content, much like a Map
        Returns:
        a reference to the node inserted

      • find

        Optional<NameTree<T>> find(net.named_data.jndn.Name query)
        Parameters:
        query - the name to use as a path through the tree
        Returns:
        an optional node; if there is no node at the end of the query, the Optional will be empty

      • delete

        Optional<NameTree<T>> delete(net.named_data.jndn.Name name)
        Parameters:
        name - the name to use as a path through the tree
        Returns:
        the removed node or an empty Optional if the node was not found

      • count

        int count()
        Returns:
        the count of all nodes in the tree below this one that are non-empty (e.g. have some content)

      • clear

        void clear()
        Remove all nodes beneath this one; will have no effect on a leaf node
